mpg123 reads one or more files (or standard input if "-" is
specified) or URIs and plays the audio stream associated with the
input on the audio device (default) or outputs them to stdout. The
file or URL is assumed to be an MPEG-1/2 Layer 3 audio bit stream.

This version has been enhanced to comply with security standards set
forth by the OpenBSD project regarding use of string functions, and
comes with a howto what to do with corrupt (ID3) headers.
